olive oil
1 potato
1 white turnip
1 packet chicken thigh
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 tsp honey
1 packet Slaw Mix
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Italian Truffle Mayonnaise
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato and kohlrabi into fries.
• Place veggie fries on a lined oven tray. Season with salt, drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.
• In the last 5 minutes of cook time, sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake until melted.

• When the fries have 15 minutes remaining, combine chicken thigh, Aussie spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil in a medium bowl.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook chicken until browned, 2 minutes each side.
• Transfer chicken to a second lined oven tray, drizzle over the honey and roast until cooked through, 10-12 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• In a second medium bowl, combine slaw mix and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Slice spiced chicken.
• Divide chicken, cheesy veggie fries and slaw between plates.
• Serve with mayonnaise. Enjoy!